article.headline: Hawaii 84, Alcorn St. 55
article.story: HONOLULU (AP)Riley Luettgerodt scored 20 points to lead Hawaii to an 84-55 win over Alcorn State for its first victory of the season Sunday. Bobby Nash scored 15 points for the Rainbow Warriors (1-2) and Stephen Verwers added 10. Anthony Ford was the only Alcorn State player in double figures with 16 points. Anthony Searcy had 10 rebounds for the Braves (0-3). Back-to-back 3-pointers by Nash sparked a six-minute, 22-4 run to give the Rainbow Warriors a 41-19 lead with 3:01 remaining in the first half. Alcorn State got to the free throw line 22 times, but converted on just nine attempts. Searcy shot just 2-of-9 from the free throw line for the Braves.
